<div id="procuretopay_trans_addgoodsreceipt">
<p><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Add New Goods Receipt</b></p>
<ol><b>To Add New Goods Receipt</b>
<li>You have to select the values of "Date", "Vendor" and "Gate Entry #" from dropdowns.</li>
<li>You can enter "Receiving Quantity", "Remarks", "Bags" and select "Bag Type" for all the POs' with the selected GE.</li><br/>
 <b>Eg:</b> If suppose the Date is "25 <sup>th</sup> June, 2011", Vendor is "Ajay", GE # is "GE-0111-0006" then you have to select <em style="color:#0066FF">25.06.2011</em> for "Date", <em style="color:#0066FF">Ajay</em> for "Vendor", <em style="color:#0066FF">GE-0111-0006</em> for "GE #".<br/>
 Let 2 POs with GE <em style="color:#0066FF">GE-0111-0006</em> were displayed with their corresponding "Accepted Quantity" values.The Receiving Quantity values are "1500","1200" , Bags are "15","12" and Bag Type is "Numbers" then ,<br/> you have to enter <em style="color:#0066FF">1500</em> for "Receiving Quantity" of first PO,<em style="color:#0066FF">1200</em> for "Receiving Quantity" of second PO, <em style="color:#0066FF">15</em> for "Bags" of first PO, <em style="color:#0066FF">12</em> for "Bags" of second PO and select <em style="color:#0066FF">Gunny Bags</em> for "Bag Type".
 <li>Once filled click on 'SAVE' button to save the Goods Receipt or 'CANCEL' to exit without saving.</li>
</ol>
<b>NOTE : </b>We can add Goods Receipt when any pending values in GateEntry are present only.
</div> <!--end of procuretopay_trans_addgoodsreceipt-->
